{
  "texts": [
    "While not denying potential health impacts, these accounts are more middle-of-the-road or self-controlled.",
    "Some participants reported that the effect of food delivery on their health is general or none.",
    "Others, however, pointed out agency, with them having the option to select healthy food when ordering or to have home meals to enjoy what they desire.",
    "The most commonly cited neutral stance was mitigation strategies, with participants sure of taking steps voluntarily to avoid unhealthy food.",
    "These responses suggest that a population of users knows possible risks but feels they can manage them."
  ]
}